1
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:05,019
[Fight for You]

2
00:01:08,810 --> 00:01:10,150
At Dou Keyi Convenience House,

3
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:12,150
we can take care of anything for you.

4
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:15,310
Anything.

5
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:22,120
[File 4: Their Relationship Begins to Change]

6
00:01:25,830 --> 00:01:27,200
There may be evidence...

7
00:01:28,170 --> 00:01:30,360
of illegal transactions inside that bear.

8
00:01:30,830 --> 00:01:32,390
But how can I get it?

9
00:01:33,180 --> 00:01:34,840
Is that his contact person?

10
00:01:34,860 --> 00:01:35,720
Wait a sec.

11
00:01:40,729 --> 00:01:43,229
Why does she look so much like that girl who was looking for her cat?

12
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:44,250
[Are you talking about me?]

13
00:01:45,130 --> 00:01:46,900
Why is she standing so close to him?

14
00:02:07,490 --> 00:02:08,590
I'm calling the police!

15
00:02:08,610 --> 00:02:09,780
How dare you rob him

16
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:10,810
in broad daylight?

17
00:02:14,270 --> 00:02:15,160
Why are you here?

18
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:15,960
Are you okay?

19
00:02:16,630 --> 00:02:17,970
I just happened to be passing by...

20
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:19,450
Doing street interviews for my thesis.

21
00:02:20,570 --> 00:02:22,100
Your job is so dangerous.

22
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,440
Is this bear covered in diamonds or something?

23
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:24,910
He was holding a knife.

24
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:26,140
Why did you rush over here?

25
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:28,030
That's nothing. Are you okay?

26
00:02:28,410 --> 00:02:29,040
I'm okay.

27
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:30,150
Are you hurt?

28
00:02:31,010 --> 00:02:32,510
You're bleeding a lot!

29
00:02:32,730 --> 00:02:33,530
Blood!

30
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:36,780
It's okay.

31
00:02:36,810 --> 00:02:38,110
The wound shouldn't be deep.

32
00:02:39,290 --> 00:02:40,060
But you,

33
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:40,960
protecting this bear like that.

34
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:42,190
Should we drop it off somewhere first?

35
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,780
I'm taking you to the hospital first!

36
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:44,780
No need!

37
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:48,130
I'm allergic to hospital disinfectants. I'd faint.

38
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:51,310
I'll see what's hidden inside this bear

39
00:02:51,329 --> 00:02:52,850
that made you protect it like that.

40
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:55,350
How can you still be smiling? You nearly scared me to death.

41
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:56,920
Calm down, calm down.

42
00:02:56,950 --> 00:02:59,070
Just treat me to something delicious tonight.

43
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:01,570
My colleagues will likely come to pick it up later.

44
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:02,290
Let's go.

45
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:33,030
Where to?

46
00:03:33,490 --> 00:03:34,360
Bathroom.

47
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:35,490
I'll go with you.

48
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:36,970
No need. I can go by myself.

49
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,100
Wait for me there.

50
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,690
Are you mad at me?

51
00:04:45,490 --> 00:04:48,010
I saw someone rushing toward you.

52
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,680
I just wanted to block him.

53
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:52,420
How could I have known he'd pull out a knife?

54
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,659
And you still rushed out despite the knife.

55
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,820
So now are you blaming me?

56
00:04:56,890 --> 00:04:58,960
Who would be foolish enough to only care about that bear?

57
00:05:02,030 --> 00:05:04,060
It wasn't foolishness. It's work.

58
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,290
Work means you have to get the job done at all costs.

59
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:10,020
Better to sacrifice your life for work, right?

60
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,420
You let yourself be a punching bag,

61
00:05:12,450 --> 00:05:13,790
kicked and beaten.

62
00:05:14,170 --> 00:05:15,270
You might be able to endure it,

63
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,400
but I can't stand watching this.

64
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,750
Why can't you stand it?

65
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:26,410
Because friends help each other in times of need.

66
00:05:29,010 --> 00:05:30,040
Are we just friends?

67
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,120
Not just friends.

68
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:56,080
Because you said...

69
00:05:57,110 --> 00:05:58,610
you are my boyfriend.

70
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:01,960
That's why you're so good to me.

71
00:06:16,690 --> 00:06:18,030
What are you doing?

72
00:06:20,030 --> 00:06:22,070
Rehearsing in advance for Grandma

73
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:24,800
so we won't slip up.

74
00:06:26,070 --> 00:06:27,070
Who would practice

75
00:06:27,340 --> 00:06:29,400
this kind of thing for their elders?

76
00:06:29,470 --> 00:06:30,300
Hei Yubo,

77
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,390
are you drunk on rubbing alcohol or something?

78
00:06:34,590 --> 00:06:35,920
You can't drink cold drinks.

79
00:06:36,540 --> 00:06:38,080
I'll make you some fish soup.

80
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:40,710
It helps wounds heal faster.

81
00:06:50,220 --> 00:06:51,060
Did you finish this bottle?

82
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,140
Just a soda.

83
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,770
I can handle a soda.

84
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:55,370
This is beer.

85
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,050
Do you not drink alcohol?

86
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:10,190
Teachers don't have freedom,

87
00:07:11,530 --> 00:07:13,430
so I chose to become a sparring partner.

88
00:07:14,030 --> 00:07:16,230
A sparring partner is the kind of job...

89
00:07:17,230 --> 00:07:19,630
where you get hit but can't hit back.

90
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:23,350
So...

91
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:26,350
don't worry about me.

92
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,240
I'm tough.

93
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:34,340
Thank you.

94
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,600
Thank you for standing in front of me.

95
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:43,320
Get up first.

96
00:07:45,159 --> 00:07:47,030
Trading your body for money

97
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:48,480
and boasting about being tough?

98
00:07:49,590 --> 00:07:50,940
I'll get you a towel.

99
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:53,070
Where are you going?

100
00:07:53,870 --> 00:07:55,070
You got hurt for me.

101
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:56,810
You bled for me.

102
00:07:57,170 --> 00:07:59,370
I have to take care of you.

103
00:07:59,370 --> 00:08:01,110
Just one bottle of beer, and you're drunk like this.

104
00:08:01,110 --> 00:08:02,640
No wonder you say you can't drink.

105
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:06,190
I'll make you some sea bass soup.

106
00:08:06,210 --> 00:08:07,280
It helps the...

107
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:09,050
wounds heal faster!

108
00:08:09,050 --> 00:08:09,950
Be careful.

109
00:08:13,990 --> 00:08:15,390
Watch your step.

110
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,040
Sea bass soup!

111
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:18,460
It'll help you heal faster!

112
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,820
Watch your step.

113
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:21,500
No, go to your room and rest.

114
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,130
Sea bass soup!

115
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,380
Good thing we didn't get tricked

116
00:08:36,409 --> 00:08:37,470
by those two teddy bears.

117
00:08:38,350 --> 00:08:41,190
There was really nothing inside that tie-wearing bear?

118
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,300
We even had it tested.

119
00:08:44,420 --> 00:08:47,050
It's just polyester fiber and glass beads.

120
00:08:47,230 --> 00:08:49,490
So we should focus on that lace-dressed bear.

121
00:08:49,710 --> 00:08:50,740
Anyway,

122
00:08:50,770 --> 00:08:52,140
try to find a way to trick

123
00:08:52,230 --> 00:08:53,930
Hei Yubo into telling you what's inside that bear

124
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,660
and how the transaction works.

125
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:02,670
I don't think Hei Yubo knows anything.

126
00:09:02,940 --> 00:09:04,510
That's why he got played.

127
00:09:04,970 --> 00:09:07,480
Don't make assumptions! Verify it!

128
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:10,470
Bai?

129
00:09:11,930 --> 00:09:12,900
Bai Zhouqi.

130
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:13,720
Yes!

131
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,030
Let me ask you:

132
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:16,950
Did you get hurt when you followed him today?

133
00:09:16,980 --> 00:09:17,990
No, no.

134
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:18,950
No Sir,

135
00:09:18,950 --> 00:09:20,160
I'll report back if anything comes up.

136
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:34,900
Did you see a cockroach again,

137
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:36,270
or are you drunk and fell?

138
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:38,600
Are you okay?

139
00:09:39,430 --> 00:09:40,330
I'm okay.

140
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:43,790
Did our floor do something to you?

141
00:09:52,410 --> 00:09:54,020
I still can't figure out

142
00:09:54,050 --> 00:09:55,750
what could be inside that bear

143
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:57,290
that would make someone try to rob it with a knife.

144
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:02,470
You delivered it back just now.

145
00:10:02,490 --> 00:10:05,040
The people at the convenience house saw you being beaten up like this

146
00:10:05,170 --> 00:10:06,500
with blood stains...

147
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,450
They didn't say anything?

148
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:18,190
Got hurt?

149
00:10:19,130 --> 00:10:19,900
I'm fine.

150
00:10:20,530 --> 00:10:21,830
Someone tried to rob the goods,

151
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:23,120
but the bear is safe.

152
00:10:23,140 --> 00:10:24,010
It's intact.

153
00:10:28,190 --> 00:10:29,240
Good job.

154
00:10:29,610 --> 00:10:30,730
Go back now.

155
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:32,080
Don't let Mr. Dou see you.

156
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:34,310
Thank you.

157
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:55,920
This is for you.

158
00:10:56,490 --> 00:10:58,090
I'm sorry you got hurt because of me.

159
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,510
What's the point of giving me money?

160
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:05,530
Before your convenience house assigns you tasks,

161
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:07,360
don't they tell you if they might be dangerous?

162
00:11:08,420 --> 00:11:10,210
It was just a delivery.

163
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:14,700
You trust them that much?

164
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:18,100
You didn't even ask about the contents before accepting the task.

165
00:11:18,620 --> 00:11:20,860
When you mail something at a convenience store,

166
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,710
the staff won't ask you what it is either, right?

167
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:31,560
What if... there's something shady in the package,

168
00:11:31,580 --> 00:11:32,980
and you end up getting arrested?

169
00:11:35,590 --> 00:11:36,960
You're overthinking.

170
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,250
Dou Keyi Convenience House

171
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:43,170
is not as simple as it seems...

172
00:11:43,690 --> 00:11:44,430
right?

173
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:50,020
The convenience house handles all kinds of requests.

174
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:52,280
Many different kinds.

175
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:57,840
Any more, and it'll break.

176
00:11:58,810 --> 00:12:01,620
If you don't want to tell me, I won't push you.

177
00:12:01,650 --> 00:12:04,070
But there are so many other job options out there.

178
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:05,980
Why the convenience house?

179
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:09,080
If, as you say,

180
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:10,760
the tasks are that simple,

181
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:13,170
how could you earn so much money from it?

182
00:12:14,330 --> 00:12:15,780
More than being a sparring partner?

183
00:12:18,630 --> 00:12:21,270
Even I was scared to see you hurt.

184
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:24,920
Imagine how worried Grandma would be if she found out.

185
00:12:26,710 --> 00:12:28,980
Actually, I don't have a choice.

186
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:33,870
My little sister has had a heart condition since she was a kid.

187
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:36,750
She's always getting hospitalized.

188
00:12:39,070 --> 00:12:41,810
Being a regular sparring partner could tide me through at first.

189
00:12:43,450 --> 00:12:45,900
But now, she needs a heart valve replacement.

190
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,360
The cost is too high.

191
00:12:48,420 --> 00:12:49,990
I didn't dare to tell Grandma,

192
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:51,260
so...

193
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:54,520
I lied and said my sister went abroad.

194
00:12:56,220 --> 00:12:57,820
Doesn't she have health insurance?

195
00:13:00,130 --> 00:13:02,690
Her condition isn't covered by it.

196
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:05,660
The artificial valve is self-paid.

197
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:08,910
Mr. Dou was kind enough to help me.

198
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:16,800
I know the risks of the convenience house.

199
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:20,280
But Mr. Dou wouldn't harm me.

200
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,810
And, more importantly, it's to save my sister.

201
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:31,240
Just doing some physical labor.

202
00:13:59,890 --> 00:14:01,810
Don't you trust people too easily?

203
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:05,040
One day, if you

204
00:14:05,190 --> 00:14:07,220
found out the real reason I approached you...

205
00:14:08,390 --> 00:14:09,820
would you be angry

206
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:10,920
and ignore me,

207
00:14:11,230 --> 00:14:12,670
or beat me up?

208
00:14:59,170 --> 00:15:00,040
No Sir.

209
00:15:02,530 --> 00:15:03,710
Didn't you say that you were fine?

210
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:04,960
I'm fine.

211
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:06,780
I just accidentally fell while tailing him.

212
00:15:06,810 --> 00:15:07,740
I'm okay. Look.

213
00:15:08,590 --> 00:15:10,100
Protect yourself.

214
00:15:10,350 --> 00:15:11,450
In our line of work,

215
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:12,940
not being calm enough is a fatal mistake.

216
00:15:16,980 --> 00:15:18,080
About what's inside that bear...

217
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,380
Hei Yubo doesn't know what's inside!

218
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:22,360
I'm warning you again!

219
00:15:22,930 --> 00:15:25,560
Be skeptical of everything.

220
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:27,590
How can you be sure that he knows nothing?

221
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,860
Since childhood, our Bai Zhouqi has always been

222
00:15:31,890 --> 00:15:33,530
easily influenced and indecisive,

223
00:15:33,550 --> 00:15:35,440
and his convictions have never been firm enough.

224
00:15:36,110 --> 00:15:38,950
Help me straighten him out.

225
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:39,870
Yes, sir.

226
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:49,980
According to the internal report,

227
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:52,300
there's a ring inside the lace-dressed bear.

228
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:54,370
Pure gold, weighing 2.74 grams.

229
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,940
The market price is less than 	$8,000.

230
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,240
It's just a ring?

231
00:15:58,560 --> 00:16:00,680
Then why all the fuss?

232
00:16:01,330 --> 00:16:02,720
It's a token of love

233
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:04,860
from a mistress to a mob boss.

234
00:16:04,980 --> 00:16:06,800
Why make such a big deal out of it,

235
00:16:06,830 --> 00:16:08,440
even going so far as to send people to steal it?

236
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:16,610
Based on what I know about Dou Keyi...

237
00:16:17,510 --> 00:16:18,850
this deal...

238
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:21,650
might be just a test.

239
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:23,080
Test?

240
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:27,650
Didn't you run into Dou Keyi at the convenience store?

241
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,240
Yeah, but I don't think he saw me.

242
00:16:32,610 --> 00:16:33,670
Are you sure?

243
00:16:33,690 --> 00:16:35,630
Dou Keyi is sly.

244
00:16:35,660 --> 00:16:37,890
He was testing whether you were sent by me.

245
00:16:40,950 --> 00:16:44,650
Now... he's telling me through this message...

246
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,990
that he already knows you're mine.

247
00:16:47,010 --> 00:16:48,480
What should we do now?

248
00:16:52,510 --> 00:16:54,540
If the enemy doesn't make a move, neither will we.

249
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:57,230
Since they're suspicious...

250
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:59,830
you need to be extra careful.

251
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:01,780
Yes, sir.

252
00:17:03,570 --> 00:17:05,359
Has Hei Yubo been up to anything lately?

253
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,000
No Sir,

254
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:09,730
I feel that Hei Yubo

255
00:17:09,730 --> 00:17:10,859
is different from those people

256
00:17:10,859 --> 00:17:11,690
at the Dou Keyi Convenience House.

257
00:17:12,630 --> 00:17:13,770
You feel?

258
00:17:22,420 --> 00:17:25,089
He... seems to trust you quite a bit, right?

259
00:17:36,270 --> 00:17:37,360
Find a chance

260
00:17:37,550 --> 00:17:38,960
to go on a task with him.

261
00:17:39,130 --> 00:17:40,070
Me?

262
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:41,890
Join him on a task?

263
00:17:43,030 --> 00:17:45,480
Since you said his tasks are so simple,

264
00:17:45,670 --> 00:17:47,040
then asking to

265
00:17:47,070 --> 00:17:48,910
experience one together

266
00:17:48,930 --> 00:17:50,060
wouldn't be too much, right?

267
00:17:51,970 --> 00:17:54,030
What if he refuses?

268
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:57,250
Doesn't that mean he's just like those people?

269
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,630
What? Is there a problem?

270
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:06,230
Bai.

271
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:10,210
Those who know are as guilty as those who commit the crime.

272
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:12,140
Don't be soft-hearted.

273
00:18:17,980 --> 00:18:19,190
Where's Dou Keyi?

274
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:21,230
I asked him to watch the store for me...

275
00:18:21,230 --> 00:18:22,260
No Sir?

276
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:24,870
He ran away before he finished the pot!

277
00:18:24,890 --> 00:18:25,830
Gosh!

278
00:18:25,860 --> 00:18:27,160
Why did you come here?

279
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:28,550
What else could I do?

280
00:18:28,910 --> 00:18:30,410
You've been avoiding me these days,

281
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:33,810
so I had to come chase after you.

282
00:18:35,810 --> 00:18:37,020
Not really.

283
00:18:37,510 --> 00:18:38,440
I... I've been busy.

284
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:46,950
I thought

285
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:48,350
things between us

286
00:18:48,370 --> 00:18:50,670
changed after that day.

287
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:00,700
Wanna breakfast?

288
00:19:01,860 --> 00:19:02,520
Mm.

289
00:19:06,730 --> 00:19:09,490
Sobered up and back to your gloomy face.

290
00:19:23,070 --> 00:19:24,370
Looking at me is supposed to fill you up or what?

291
00:19:27,950 --> 00:19:28,880
Well...

292
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:30,460
I'm sorry about yesterday.

293
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:34,300
Sorry for what part?

294
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:36,630
Grabbing me and not letting go?

295
00:19:36,650 --> 00:19:38,460
Or jumping on me?

296
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:40,210
Or...

297
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,080
What?

298
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,300
You think you can just kiss people when you're drunk?

299
00:20:07,980 --> 00:20:09,280
You kissed me, and now you're running away.

300
00:20:09,730 --> 00:20:11,870
Didn't you say we should practice for Grandma?

301
00:20:12,830 --> 00:20:14,420
When I get drunk, I get a bit...

302
00:20:14,510 --> 00:20:15,780
confused about the situation.

303
00:20:16,170 --> 00:20:17,010
I'm sorry.

304
00:20:20,050 --> 00:20:21,050
Are you going to take responsibility?

305
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:26,200
So are you going to take responsibility or not?

306
00:20:26,220 --> 00:20:27,290
I'm going to be late.

307
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:28,450
Say it...

308
00:20:28,490 --> 00:20:31,240
say that our relationship has changed now.

309
00:20:32,530 --> 00:20:34,500
Don't ignore me.

310
00:20:34,530 --> 00:20:35,600
So now

311
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,100
who is ignoring whom?

312
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:38,160
Grandma,

313
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:39,990
he won't let me accompany him to work.

314
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,040
Isn't it good to have someone to work alongside you?

315
00:20:42,060 --> 00:20:43,200
What's wrong with you?

316
00:20:43,230 --> 00:20:45,140
Yeah. A couple should experience life together

317
00:20:45,170 --> 00:20:46,580
to build better rapport for the future together.

318
00:20:46,580 --> 00:20:47,340
That's right!

319
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:49,110
Madam.

320
00:20:49,730 --> 00:20:50,330
Coming!

321
00:20:50,660 --> 00:20:51,730
I'm leaving you two.

322
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,400
Come on, let's go home.

323
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:06,780
That day, you said our relationship

324
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:08,870
started to be different.

325
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:10,730
Different how?

326
00:21:13,450 --> 00:21:15,600
Even though we're not really dating,

327
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:16,900
we live together,

328
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:17,820
we've kissed,

329
00:21:17,850 --> 00:21:19,110
and we've gone through hardships together.

330
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:20,550
That changed our relationship, right?

331
00:21:55,870 --> 00:21:57,090
Why are you backing away from me?

332
00:21:58,100 --> 00:21:59,840
Why are you leaning in so close?

333
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:02,870
What do you want me to do?

334
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:31,840
What kind of task is it, really?

335
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:34,460
[Preview]

336
00:22:31,860 --> 00:22:32,900
Seduction?

337
00:22:32,930 --> 00:22:34,740
If there's a task, we'll do it together.

338
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:36,530
Look at that man.

339
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:39,380
From now on,

340
00:22:39,410 --> 00:22:42,010
we're 100% on the same side.

341
00:22:42,030 --> 00:22:43,580
The beginning is always the hardest.

342
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:46,400
The initial contact is crucial.

343
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,500
Which parts are real

344
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:51,370
and which parts are fake?

345
00:22:52,410 --> 00:22:53,580
If this continues,

346
00:22:54,010 --> 00:22:54,980
I might really fall for you.